      <title>Hope vs Wish</title>
      <link href="/2023/10/16/Hope&amp;Wish/"/>
      <url>/2023/10/16/Hope&amp;Wish/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="The-Difference-Between-Hope-and-Wish"><a href="#The-Difference-Between-Hope-and-Wish" class="headerlink" title="The Difference Between Hope and Wish"></a>The Difference Between Hope and Wish</h1><h3 id="hope-possibly-achieved-through-hard-work"><a href="#hope-possibly-achieved-through-hard-work" class="headerlink" title="hope: possibly achieved through hard work"></a>hope: possibly achieved through hard work</h3><ol><li>hope to do sth.<br> e.g. I hope to see you again soon.</li><li>hope + clause<br> e.g. I hope that I can pass the exam tomorrow.</li></ol><h3 id="wish-an-intention-that-may-fail"><a href="#wish-an-intention-that-may-fail" class="headerlink" title="wish: an intention that may fail"></a>wish: an intention that may fail</h3><ol><li>wish (sb.) to do sth.<br> e.g. I wish the manager to get informed at once.</li><li>wish + n.<br> e.g. We wish you both health and longevity.</li><li>wish sth. done<br> e.g. I wish the letter posted at once.</li><li>wish + clause<br> e.g. I wish you wouldn’t leave your clothes all over the floor.<code>(a kind of request)</code></li></ol>]]></content>
      
      
      
