      <title>Apple Watch Comments</title>
      <link href="/2023/09/25/Apple-Watch-Comments/"/>
      <url>/2023/09/25/Apple-Watch-Comments/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Having weared new watch for a day, I do love it so much! It would be quite convenient for me to tap on and tap off when taking public transit. What makes me more exciting is that I’ve linked my student card to the electronic transportation card, which means I can tap with my watch and pay on campus. However, since Weixin Pay is more common in my life, I also added it to the face so that it won’t take long to open payment code.</p><p>Everything is new, including the workout track and handwashing timer. Double pinch to confirm is also a fantastic interaction. What is kind like a pity is that I cannot find a route on my watch once it is diconnected to WLAN. I can only set it up on my phone and it will automatically show on the watch. I still need to adjust to it.</p><p>Let me show it off at the end of the post!<br><img src="AppleWatch.png" class="lazyload placeholder" data-srcset="AppleWatch.png" srcset="https://pic1.zhimg.com/v2-cd38920285d125be80b3eb504052c550_b.webp" alt="P.S. iOS 17 is not a good operation system, at least these weeks, for me"></p>]]></content>
      
      
      
